To capatilize
{% set myText = "hello world" %}
{{ myText | capitalize }}

To convert to lowercase
{% set myText = "HELLO WORLD" %}
{{ myText | lower }}

Capitalizes the first letter of each word in the text.
{% set myText = "hello world" %}
{{ myText | title }}

Replaces occurrences of a substring with another substring.
{% set myText = "Hello world" %}
{{ myText | replace("world", "universe") }}

Limits the text to a specified length and adds an ellipsis if it exceeds that length.
{% set myText = "This is a long sentence." %}
{{ myText | truncate(10) }}

Retrieves the length of a string.
{% set myText = "Hello world" %}
{{ myText | length }}

 Extracts a portion of a string based on start and end indices.
{% set myText = "Hello world" %}
{{ myText | slice(0, 5) }}

 Removes leading and trailing whitespace from a string.
{% set myText = "   Hello world    " %}
{{ myText | trim }}

Concatenates multiple strings with a specified separator.
{% set fruits = ["apple", "banana", "orange"] %}
{{ fruits | join(", ") }}

Splits a string into an array based on a specified separator.
{% set myText = "apple,banana,orange" %}
{% set myArray = myText | split(",") %}
{{ myArray }}

 Sets a default value if a variable is not defined or is empty.
{% set myText = "" %}
{{ myText | default("No text available") }}

Reverses the order of characters in a string.
{% set myText = "Hello world" %}
{{ myText | reverse }}

URL-encodes a string.
{% set myText = "Hello world!" %}
{{ myText | urlencode }}

Counts the number of words in a string.
{% set myText = "This is a sentence." %}
{{ myText | wordcount }}

Limits the text to a specified number of words and adds an ellipsis if it exceeds that limit.
{% set myText = "This is a long sentence with many words." %}
{{ myText | truncatewords(5) }}











